===Etymology 1===
<div style="float:right;">
[[File:HinaDolls-Emperor-Empress-topplatform2011.jpg|thumb|right|{{lang|ja|雛}} (''hina'', ''hīna''): Emperor and Empress ''hina'' dolls, in front of gold screens. The optional lampstands are also partially visible.]]
</div>
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|ひな}}

&#42;{{IPAchar|/pina/}} → {{IPAchar|/fina/}} → {{IPAchar|/hina/}}

Appears to be from {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=ひな|-}}. The derivative form ''hiwina'' (later ''hīna'') appears in ''{{w|The Tale of Genji}}'', dated to before 1021.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

====Pronunciation====
{{ja-pron|ひな|acc=1|acc_ref=DJR,NHK}}

====Noun====
{{ja-noun|ひな}}

# a type of small [[doll]], typically standing upright in the Heian period, changing style to a seated posture in the Muromachi period
# short for {{m|ja|雛祭り|tr=Hina matsuri}}
# a [[chick]], a young [[bird]]: see the reading ''hiyoko'' below

====Prefix====
{{ja-pos|prefix|ひな}}

# [[diminutive]] prefix, carrying [[favorable]] connotations such as a sense of [[cuteness]]

