===Etymology 2===
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|ひいな}}

&#42;{{IPAchar|/pipina/}} → &#42;{{IPAchar|/fifina/}} → {{IPAchar|/fiwina/}} → {{IPAchar|/hiːna/}}

Possibly an alteration of a reduplicated form ''hinahina''.

====Pronunciation====
{{ja-pron|ひいな|acc=1}}

====Noun====
{{ja-noun|ひいな|hhira=ひひな}}

# {{lb|ja|archaic|sort=ひいな}} [[doll]]

=====Usage notes=====
This reading with the long ''ī'' is archaic. In modern Japanese, the shorter reading ''hina'' is more common for this sense.

=====Derived terms=====
{{col-top|2|Derived terms using {{lang|ja|雛}} (''hīna'')}}
