* {{ja-r|雛衣|ひいなぎぬ}}: [[clothes]] for a ''hina'' [[doll]]
* {{ja-r|雛草|ひいなぐさ}}: alternate name for {{m|ja|髢草|tr=kamojigusa}}, a type of [[wild]] [[rye]] or [[wheatgrass]]
* {{ja-r|雛本|ひいなぼん}}: a type of small children's [[book]] in the Edo period used at [[Hina matsuri]] and when [[play house|playing house]]
* {{ja-r|雛祭り|^ひいな まつり|rom=-}}, {{ja-r|雛祭|^ひいな まつり}}: [[girl|Girl]]'s [[day|Day]], the [[doll]] [[festival]]
* {{ja-r|雛屋|ひいなや}}: a [[dollhouse]] for ''hina'' [[doll]]s; a store selling ''hina'' dolls
{{col-bottom}}

===Etymology 3===
<div style="float:right;">
[[Image:Chick.jpg|thumb|right|{{lang|ja|雛}} (''hiyoko''): A baby chicken (chick), ''Gallus gallus domesticus'']]
</div>
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|ひよこ}}

&#42;{{IPAchar|/pijoko/}} → {{IPAchar|/fijoko/}} → {{IPAchar|/hijoko/}}

Compound of {{compound|ja|sort=ひよこ|ひよ|tr1=piyo → hiyo|t1=[[onomatopoeia]] for the sound a chick makes|子|tr2=ko|t2=diminutive suffix}}. Compare {{ja-r|ぴよぴよ|t=[[tweet|tweet-tweet]]; [[cheep|cheep-cheep]]}} or {{m|en|peep}}.

Possibly related to {{cog|okm|비〮육}}, whence modern {{cog|ko|병아리|t=chick}}.

